<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-11-19T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-11-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/1679: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Collier</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-11-19T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 19,
                                        1925—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>74. Embassy’s No. 118, November 12, 3 p.m. I should be glad to have you
                            discuss matter in friendly informal way with Chilean Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs. This will give him opportunity of his own volition to
                            correct the existing abuses. Continue to keep Department informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>